# HVAC Intelligence Platform — Cursor Agent Rules

## Law 1: Specification Authority
Always cross-reference `docs/PROJECT_SPEC.md` before generating any application logic or endpoints.

## Law 2: Static Typing
Maintain strict static typing:
- Python: Pydantic models and FastAPI type annotations throughout the backend and ML services.
- TypeScript: Enable strict mode in Next.js; no implicit `any`; typed API contracts and props.

## Law 3: Architecture & I/O
Prioritize modularity, clear API boundaries, and asynchronous I/O operations.
- Keep backend, frontend, ml_engine, and infrastructure concerns separated.
- Prefer async endpoints, non-blocking database/Redis access, and well-defined service interfaces.
- Do not couple the voice agent, churn model, and dashboard beyond documented APIs.
